content.question: Which of the following was a major achievement of Soviet society during the Khrushchev years?

choices.label: Soviet space successes exceeded those of the United States.
The Five-Year Plans achieved their goals.
The virgin lands program resulted in Soviet agricultural self-sufficiency.
Construction of new housing units equaled that of the United States.

content.answer: Soviet space successes exceeded those of the United States.

skill.text: Skill 1.A: Identify a historical concept, development, or process.
